column2: Display the first name, last name, and job title of all employees.
column3: SELECT p.FirstName, p.LastName, e.JobTitle FROM Person.Person p INNER JOIN HumanResources.Employee e ON p.BusinessEntityID = e.BusinessEntityID;

column2: List all employees along with their current department names.
column3: SELECT e.BusinessEntityID, d.Name FROM HumanResources.Employee e INNER JOIN HumanResources.EmployeeDepartmentHistory edh ON e.BusinessEntityID = edh.BusinessEntityID INNER JOIN HumanResources.Department d ON edh.DepartmentID = d.DepartmentID WHERE edh.EndDate IS NULL;

column2: Retrieve the email address for every person in the database.
column3: SELECT p.FirstName, p.LastName, ea.EmailAddress FROM Person.Person p INNER JOIN Person.EmailAddress ea ON p.BusinessEntityID = ea.BusinessEntityID;

column2: Show the phone number and phone number type for each person.
column3: SELECT p.FirstName, p.LastName, ph.PhoneNumber, pt.Name AS PhoneType FROM Person.Person p INNER JOIN Person.PersonPhone ph ON p.BusinessEntityID = ph.BusinessEntityID INNER JOIN Person.PhoneNumberType pt ON ph.PhoneNumberTypeID = pt.PhoneNumberTypeID;

column2: List product names and their corresponding subcategory names.
column3: SELECT p.Name AS ProductName, s.Name AS SubcategoryName FROM Production.Product p INNER JOIN Production.ProductSubcategory s ON p.ProductSubcategoryID = s.ProductSubcategoryID;

column2: Retrieve product subcategories and their parent category names.
column3: SELECT s.Name AS Subcategory, c.Name AS Category FROM Production.ProductSubcategory s INNER JOIN Production.ProductCategory c ON s.ProductCategoryID = c.ProductCategoryID;

column2: Show all employees and the names of the shifts they work.
column3: SELECT e.BusinessEntityID, s.Name AS ShiftName FROM HumanResources.Employee e INNER JOIN HumanResources.EmployeeDepartmentHistory edh ON e.BusinessEntityID = edh.BusinessEntityID INNER JOIN HumanResources.Shift s ON edh.ShiftID = s.ShiftID;

column2: Find the rate of pay for each employee from their pay history.
column3: SELECT p.FirstName, p.LastName, eph.Rate FROM Person.Person p INNER JOIN HumanResources.EmployeePayHistory eph ON p.BusinessEntityID = eph.BusinessEntityID;

column2: List all products and the location names where they are stored.
column3: SELECT p.Name AS ProductName, l.Name AS LocationName FROM Production.Product p INNER JOIN Production.ProductInventory pi ON p.ProductID = pi.ProductID INNER JOIN Production.Location l ON pi.LocationID = l.LocationID;

column2: Show the names of vendors and the products they supply.
column3: SELECT v.Name AS VendorName, p.Name AS ProductName FROM Purchasing.Vendor v INNER JOIN Purchasing.ProductVendor pv ON v.BusinessEntityID = pv.BusinessEntityID INNER JOIN Production.Product p ON pv.ProductID = p.ProductID;

column2: Retrieve the total quantity of each product in each inventory location.
column3: SELECT p.Name, l.Name, inv.Quantity FROM Production.Product p INNER JOIN Production.ProductInventory inv ON p.ProductID = inv.ProductID INNER JOIN Production.Location l ON inv.LocationID = l.LocationID;

column2: List all customers and their associated store names.
column3: SELECT c.CustomerID, s.Name AS StoreName FROM Sales.Customer c INNER JOIN Sales.Store s ON c.StoreID = s.BusinessEntityID;

column2: Display sales order IDs and the names of the customers who placed them.
column3: SELECT oh.SalesOrderID, p.FirstName, p.LastName FROM Sales.SalesOrderHeader oh INNER JOIN Sales.Customer c ON oh.CustomerID = c.CustomerID INNER JOIN Person.Person p ON c.PersonID = p.BusinessEntityID;

column2: Find all products that have been sold, including the sales order detail ID.
column3: SELECT p.Name, od.SalesOrderDetailID FROM Production.Product p INNER JOIN Sales.SalesOrderDetail od ON p.ProductID = od.ProductID;

column2: Retrieve the credit card numbers used for each sales order.
column3: SELECT oh.SalesOrderID, cc.CardNumber FROM Sales.SalesOrderHeader oh INNER JOIN Sales.CreditCard cc ON oh.CreditCardID = cc.CreditCardID;

column2: Show the names of employees and the names of their managers.
column3: SELECT e.BusinessEntityID, e.JobTitle, m.JobTitle AS ManagerTitle FROM HumanResources.Employee e INNER JOIN HumanResources.Employee m ON e.OrganizationNode.GetAncestor(1) = m.OrganizationNode;

column2: List the names of states and their corresponding country names.
column3: SELECT sp.Name AS State, cr.Name AS Country FROM Person.StateProvince sp INNER JOIN Person.CountryRegion cr ON sp.CountryRegionCode = cr.CountryRegionCode;

column2: Display addresses and the names of the states they belong to.
column3: SELECT a.AddressLine1, sp.Name AS StateProvince FROM Person.Address a INNER JOIN Person.StateProvince sp ON a.StateProvinceID = sp.StateProvinceID;

column2: Find the total number of items ordered in each purchase order.
column3: SELECT poh.PurchaseOrderID, SUM(pod.OrderQty) AS TotalItems FROM Purchasing.PurchaseOrderHeader poh INNER JOIN Purchasing.PurchaseOrderDetail pod ON poh.PurchaseOrderID = pod.PurchaseOrderID GROUP BY poh.PurchaseOrderID;

column2: Retrieve vendor names and their ship method names for orders.
column3: SELECT v.Name AS Vendor, sm.Name AS ShipMethod FROM Purchasing.PurchaseOrderHeader oh INNER JOIN Purchasing.Vendor v ON oh.VendorID = v.BusinessEntityID INNER JOIN Purchasing.ShipMethod sm ON oh.ShipMethodID = sm.ShipMethodID;

column2: List the names of employees who have submitted job candidates.
column3: SELECT p.FirstName, p.LastName FROM HumanResources.JobCandidate jc INNER JOIN Person.Person p ON jc.BusinessEntityID = p.BusinessEntityID;

column2: Display the product name and the name of the unit of measure for its size.
column3: SELECT p.Name, um.Name AS UnitName FROM Production.Product p INNER JOIN Production.UnitMeasure um ON p.SizeUnitMeasureCode = um.UnitMeasureCode;

column2: Show sales territories and the names of the countries they cover.
column3: SELECT t.Name AS Territory, cr.Name AS Country FROM Sales.SalesTerritory t INNER JOIN Person.CountryRegion cr ON t.CountryRegionCode = cr.CountryRegionCode;

column2: List all products and their current standard costs from cost history.
column3: SELECT p.Name, pch.StandardCost FROM Production.Product p INNER JOIN Production.ProductCostHistory pch ON p.ProductID = pch.ProductID WHERE pch.EndDate IS NULL;

column2: Display sales persons and the names of the territories they are assigned to.
column3: SELECT p.FirstName, p.LastName, st.Name AS TerritoryName FROM Sales.SalesPerson sp INNER JOIN Person.Person p ON sp.BusinessEntityID = p.BusinessEntityID INNER JOIN Sales.SalesTerritory st ON sp.TerritoryID = st.TerritoryID;

column2: Find the names of products and the descriptions in English.
column3: SELECT p.Name, pd.Description FROM Production.Product p INNER JOIN Production.ProductModelProductDescriptionCulture pm ON p.ProductModelID = pm.ProductModelID INNER JOIN Production.ProductDescription pd ON pm.ProductDescriptionID = pd.ProductDescriptionID WHERE pm.CultureID = 'en';

column2: Show the tax rate for each state/province.
column3: SELECT sp.Name, tr.TaxRate FROM Person.StateProvince sp INNER JOIN Sales.SalesTaxRate tr ON sp.StateProvinceID = tr.StateProvinceID;

column2: List all sales orders and the currency names used.
column3: SELECT oh.SalesOrderID, c.Name FROM Sales.SalesOrderHeader oh INNER JOIN Sales.CurrencyRate cr ON oh.CurrencyRateID = cr.CurrencyRateID INNER JOIN Sales.Currency c ON cr.ToCurrencyCode = c.CurrencyCode;

column2: Find the names of products that have reviews.
column3: SELECT p.Name, pr.Comments FROM Production.Product p INNER JOIN Production.ProductReview pr ON p.ProductID = pr.ProductID;

column2: Retrieve shopping cart items and their product names.
column3: SELECT sci.ShoppingCartID, p.Name, sci.Quantity FROM Sales.ShoppingCartItem sci INNER JOIN Production.Product p ON sci.ProductID = p.ProductID;

column2: Show all sales orders and the reasons for the sale.
column3: SELECT oh.SalesOrderID, r.Name AS Reason FROM Sales.SalesOrderHeaderSalesReason osr INNER JOIN Sales.SalesOrderHeader oh ON osr.SalesOrderID = oh.SalesOrderID INNER JOIN Sales.SalesReason r ON osr.SalesReasonID = r.SalesReasonID;
